{
  "texts": [
    "We report the human agreement in terms of the average F1 score for this validation set in Table 4.",
    "We also include the result of o3-mini, which is a strong reasoning model used in AdvancedIF as a reference.",
    "We can see that the finetuned rubric verifier achieves a significantly higher human agreement (0.728) than the vanilla LLM judge (0.515), and is on par with O3-mini (0.723).",
    "Specifically, the SFT stage can increase the performance from 0.515 to 0.656, and RL can further increase the accuracy.",
    "This demonstrates that both SFT and RL are required to effectively enhance the capability of LLMs in understanding and applying rubrics to evaluate responses."
  ]
}